content:
Can you provide me with the name of the film director who has won multiple Oscars and is famous for his science-fiction and thriller movies, including "Inception," "The Dark Knight," and "Interstellar," and who has also directed a film that won the Cannes Film Festival's Palme d'Or award? Additionally, can you provide me with the year the movie that won the Palme d'Or award was released? Here is some Scala code that might help you find the answer. Please also include the genres of the movies mentioned in the question and the name of the director who directed "Pulp Fiction." 
val films = List(
  ("Inception", List("Science fiction", "Thriller")),
  ("The Dark Knight", List("Action", "Crime", "Drama")),
  ("Interstellar", List("Adventure", "Drama", "Sci-Fi")),
  ("Pulp Fiction", List("Crime", "Drama"))
)
val directors = Map(
  "Christopher Nolan" -> List("Inception", "The Dark Knight", "Interstellar"),
  "Quentin Tarantino" -> List("Pulp Fiction", "Kill Bill", "Django Unchained"),
  "Spike Lee" -> List("Do the Right Thing", "Malcolm X", "BlacKkKlansman")
)
val palmeDOr = Map(
  "Apocalypse Now" -> 1979,
  "The Tree of Life" -> 2011,
  "Pulp Fiction" -> 1994,
  "The Piano" -> 1993,
  "Taxi Driver" -> 1976,
  "MASH" -> 1970,
  "La Dolce Vita" -> 1960,
  "The Cranes Are Flying" -> 1957
)
// Find the director who matches the criteria
val director = directors.find { case (name, films) =>
  films.contains("Inception") && films.contains("The Dark Knight") &&
  films.contains("Interstellar") && palmeDOr.contains(name)
}
// Print the director's name and the year the movie won the Palme d'Or award
director match {
  case Some((name, _)) => {
    println(name)
    palmeDOr.get(name) match {
      case Some(year) => println(year)
      case None => println("Year not found")
    }
  }
  case None => println("Director not found")
}
